1
00:00:01,126 --> 00:00:03,170
Doctor, it's Martha.

2
00:00:04,254 --> 00:00:06,089
And I'm bringing you back to Earth.

3
00:00:06,507 --> 00:00:09,384
52 deaths at the exact
same moment worldwide.

4
00:00:09,468 --> 00:00:11,053
They were all inside their cars.

5
00:00:11,136 --> 00:00:12,429
They were all fitted with Atmos.

6
00:00:12,596 --> 00:00:15,349
Atmos can be threaded through
any and every make of car.

7
00:00:15,766 --> 00:00:16,808
Get back.

8
00:00:16,892 --> 00:00:20,395
Then they've got poisonous gas
in every car on Earth.

9
00:00:20,771 --> 00:00:21,813
Sontaran!

10
00:00:21,897 --> 00:00:24,483
General Staal,
of the 10th Sontaran Fleet.

11
00:00:27,903 --> 00:00:31,031
-Oh, this is Ross. Say hello, Ross.
-Good afternoon, sir.

12
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:35,410
What is that?

13
00:00:35,494 --> 00:00:38,455
Soon, that will be you.

14
00:00:38,914 --> 00:00:40,040
Now we begin.

15
00:00:40,123 --> 00:00:42,626
Martha, tell Colonel Mace
it's the Sontarans.

16
00:00:42,793 --> 00:00:44,336
They're in the file. Code Red Sontarans.

17
00:00:44,461 --> 00:00:46,838
But if they're inside the factory,
tell him not to start shooting.

18
00:00:46,964 --> 00:00:48,215
UNIT will get massacred.

19
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:50,133
Code Red Sontaran. Gotcha.

20
00:00:50,217 --> 00:00:52,386
-Found anything yet?
-Nothing to report.

21
00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:55,055
Prepare the subjugation of Earth.

22
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:58,517
-(CHANTING) Sontar-ha!
-ALL: (CHANTING) Sontar-ha!

23
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,561
(COUGHING AND CHOKING)

24
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,604
DONNA: Doctor!

25
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:09,111
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

26
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:45,063
DONNA: Doctor! Doctor!

27
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:49,693
It won't open!

28
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:58,952
Well, don't just stand there.
Get him out.

29
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:01,955
All soldiers to a door.

30
00:02:02,039 --> 00:02:05,125
Make the factory secure,
and take positions on the ground floor!

31
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:08,003
Wicowsky, take the soldiers
into the factory.

32
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:10,922
Make the area secure.
Seal off doors and windows.

33
00:02:11,048 --> 00:02:13,967
We've tried everything!
It just won't stop!

34
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:17,512
What have we got?

35
00:02:17,596 --> 00:02:19,222
Atmos is running wild, sir.

36
00:02:19,306 --> 00:02:23,018
It can't be stopped. It's everywhere.
The whole planet.

37
00:02:42,913 --> 00:02:43,955
Thanks.

38
00:02:44,081 --> 00:02:46,500
-I can't believe you've got an axe.
-Burglars.

39
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:49,002
Get inside the house. Just try
to close off the doors and windows.

40
00:02:49,086 --> 00:02:52,047
Doctor, this is all I could find
that hasn't got Atmos.

41
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:54,383
-Donna, are you coming?
-Yeah.

42
00:02:54,466 --> 00:02:56,468
Donna, don't go!

43
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:58,428
Look what happens every time
that Doctor appears.

44
00:02:58,512 --> 00:02:59,680
Stay with us, please.

45
00:02:59,763 --> 00:03:00,931
-You go, my darling.
-Dad!

46
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:02,933
Don't listen to her!

47
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:06,478
You go with the Doctor! That's my girl!

48
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:10,482
Bye!

49
00:03:25,330 --> 00:03:26,957
(ALARM BLARING)

50
00:03:52,441 --> 00:03:55,235
Success. The operative has
the necessary information.

51
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:58,238
Good work, for a female.
Now she must be protected.

52
00:03:58,321 --> 00:04:00,741
I will prepare an attack squad.

53
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,994
This is it, isn't it?

54
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:07,456
Oh, man, this is war!

55
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:09,332
And how does it feel, boy?

56
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,876
Magnificent.

57
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:15,046
The government has declared
a state of emergency.

58
00:04:15,172 --> 00:04:20,093
People are being told to stay away from
all cars with Atmos devices attached.

59
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:22,554
The gas appears to be toxic.

60
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:26,099
We are warning anyone and everyone,
stay away from the cars.

61
00:04:26,183 --> 00:04:28,727
Repeat, stay away from your cars.

62
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,444
Ross, look after yourself.
Get inside the building.

63
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:38,862
Will do.

64
00:04:39,196 --> 00:04:40,614
Greyhound 40, this is Trap One.

65
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:43,950
I've just returned the Doctor to base,
safe and sound. Over.

66
00:04:44,034 --> 00:04:46,036
Trap One, received. Over.

67
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:49,998
Sir, a message from the Doctor.
He says Code Red Sontaran.

68
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:55,712
All troops, Code Red Sontaran.
Code Red Sontaran.

69
00:04:56,046 --> 00:04:57,214
The air is disgusting.

70
00:04:57,339 --> 00:04:59,382
It's not so bad for me.
Go on, get inside the Tardis.

71
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:02,093
Oh! I've never given you a key.

72
00:05:02,219 --> 00:05:04,513
Keep that. Go on, that's yours.
Quite a big moment, really.

73
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:08,642
Yeah, maybe we'll get sentimental after
the world's finished choking to death.

74
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:10,060
Good idea.

75
00:05:10,185 --> 00:05:11,561
Where are you going?

76
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:13,355
To stop a war!

77
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:17,901
(COUGHING)

78
00:05:29,955 --> 00:05:30,997
Fine then, here I am!

79
00:05:31,122 --> 00:05:34,334
Good. Whatever you do, Colonel Mace,
do not engage the Sontarans in battle.

80
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:36,127
There is nothing they like better
than a war.

81
00:05:36,211 --> 00:05:38,338
-Just leave this to me.
-And what are you going to do?

82
00:05:38,463 --> 00:05:42,259
I've got the Tardis.
I'm going to get on board their ship.

83
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:46,471
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

84
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:49,808
Come on.

85
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:54,604
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

86
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:10,620
Ready for transport.

87
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:21,590
(CRASHING)

88
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:31,474
The spoils of war!

89
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:35,937
The Doctor's infamous vessel
in Sontaran hands.

90
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:38,398
It's time I made a move, sir.

91
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:39,983
I have soldiers of my own.

92
00:06:40,108 --> 00:06:42,485
I'LL tell them of the honour
and the glory, sir.

93
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:45,530
I'll tell them the planet fall is coming.

94
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:51,953
He is behaving
exactly as predicted, sir.

95
00:06:52,037 --> 00:06:55,415
None of the humans can guess
our true purpose.

96
00:07:00,837 --> 00:07:02,839
But where's the Tardis?

97
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:04,966
Taste that, in the air.

98
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,511
Blah, blah, that sort of metal tang.

99
00:07:09,512 --> 00:07:11,306
Teleport exchange.

100
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:15,185
It's the Sontarans. They've taken it.

101
00:07:16,436 --> 00:07:19,022
I'm stuck on Earth, like...

102
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:23,318
Like an ordinary person, like a human.
How rubbish is that?

103
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:25,695
Sorry, no offence, but, come on!

104
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:28,198
-So, what do we do?
-Well...

105
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:32,202
I mean, it's shielded,
they could never detect it.

106
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:35,497
What?

107
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,582
I was just wondering,
have you phoned your family and Tom?

108
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:38,792
No. What for?

109
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:41,252
The gas. Tell them to stay inside.

110
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:45,131
Course I will, yeah,
but what about Donna?

111
00:07:45,215 --> 00:07:46,299
I mean, where's she?

112
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:48,969
Oh, she's gone home.

113
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:52,263
She's not like you. She's not a soldier.

114
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:54,724
Right, so, avanti/

115
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:05,902
Leave it!

116
00:08:06,403 --> 00:08:07,737
Turn away!

117
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:10,615
Civilisation is falling.

118
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,159
But it's all over the news, sir.
It's everywhere.

119
00:08:13,243 --> 00:08:15,120
Paris and New York...

120
00:08:16,746 --> 00:08:19,249
It's time I told you. All of you!

121
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:21,918
It's time I revealed what
our work has been for.

122
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:23,586
Change of plan!

123
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:25,338
Good to have you
fighting alongside us, Doctor.

124
00:08:25,422 --> 00:08:26,631
Not fighting.

125
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:28,925
I'm not-fighting, as in
not-hyphen-fighting. Got it?

126
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,553
Now, does anyone know
what this gas is yet?

127
00:08:31,636 --> 00:08:32,846
We're working on it.

128
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:36,725
It's harmful, but not lethal
until it reaches 80% density.

129
00:08:36,850 --> 00:08:39,769
We're having the first reports of deaths
from the centre of Tokyo city.

130
00:08:39,853 --> 00:08:41,229
Who are you?

131
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:42,355
Captain Marion Price, sir.

132
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:44,399
Oh, put your hand down. Don't salute.

133
00:08:44,482 --> 00:08:46,443
Jodrell Bank's traced
the signal, Doctor,

134
00:08:46,568 --> 00:08:48,278
coming from 5,000 miles
above the Earth.

135
00:08:48,403 --> 00:08:51,573
We're guessing that's what
triggered the cars.

136
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:53,199
The Sontaran ship.

137
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:55,827
NATO's gone to DEFCON 1.
We're preparing a strike.

138
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:58,455
You can't do that. Nuclear missiles
won't even scratch the surface.

139
00:08:58,538 --> 00:08:59,622
Let me talk to the Sontarans.

140
00:08:59,706 --> 00:09:01,875
You're not authorised to speak
on behalf of the Earth.

141
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:04,544
I've got that authority.
I earned that a long time ago.

142
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:06,129
Calling the Sontaran command ship,

143
00:09:06,254 --> 00:09:09,632
under Jurisdiction 2 of
the Intergalactic Rules of Engagement.

144
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:11,509
This is the Doctor.

145
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:15,597
Doctor, I'm here! Can you hear me?

146
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:18,516
Doctor, breathing your last?

147
00:09:18,808 --> 00:09:21,311
My God, they're like trolls.

148
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:23,646
Yeah, loving the diplomacy, mate.

149
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:26,566
So, tell me, General Staal,

150
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:29,360
since when did you lot become cowards?

151
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:31,446
How dare you?

152
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:32,947
Oh, that's diplomacy.

153
00:09:33,073 --> 00:09:35,408
Doctor, you impugn my honour!

154
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:38,036
Yeah, I'm really glad
you didn't say "belittle"

155
00:09:38,161 --> 00:09:39,829
'cause then I'd have a field day.

156
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:43,708
But poison gas? That's the weapon of
a coward and you know it.

157
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:47,212
Staal, you could blast this planet
out of the sky,

158
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:50,090
and yet you're sitting up above
watching it die.

159
00:09:50,173 --> 00:09:51,216
Where's the fight in that?

160
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:53,134
Where's the honour?

161
00:09:53,301 --> 00:09:56,221
Or, are you lot planning something else?

162
00:09:56,888 --> 00:09:58,681
"Cause this isn't normal
Sontaran warfare.

163
00:09:58,765 --> 00:10:00,225
What are you lot up to?

164
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:04,521
A general would be unwise to reveal
his strategy to the opposing forces.

165
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:08,358
Ah, the war's not going so well, then.
Losing, are we?

166
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:11,277
-Such a suggestion is impossible!
-What war?

167
00:10:11,361 --> 00:10:14,197
The war between the Sontarans
and the Rutans.

168
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:18,701
It's been raging, far out in the stars,
for 50,000 years.

169
00:10:18,827 --> 00:10:23,081
50,000 years of bloodshed, and for what?

170
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,624
For victory.

171
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:27,544
(CHANTING) Sontar-ha! Sontara-ha!

172
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:32,382
(ALL CHANTING) Sontar-ha! Sontar-ha!
Sontar-ha! Sontara-ha!

173
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:34,217
Give me a break.

174
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:36,553
Boys and girls!

175
00:10:36,928 --> 00:10:39,597
Doctor, I would seriously recommend
that this dialogue

176
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:42,725
is handled by
official Earth representation.

177
00:10:42,809 --> 00:10:43,852
Finished?

178
00:10:43,935 --> 00:10:47,897
You will not be so quick to ridicule
when you see our prize.

179
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:49,440
Behold!

180
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:54,571
We are the first Sontarans in history
to capture a Tardis.

181
00:10:54,863 --> 00:11:00,076
Well, as prizes go, that's noble.

182
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:04,914
As they say in Latin, dona nobis pacem.

183
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:07,667
That's me. I'm here!

184
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,211
Did you never wonder about its design?
It's a phone box.

185
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:13,464
It contains a phone,
a telephonic device for communication.

186
00:11:13,548 --> 00:11:15,383
Sort of symbolic.

187
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:18,678
Like, if only we could communicate,
you and 1.

188
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:21,347
STAAL: All you have communicated
is your distress, Doctor...

189
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:22,891
Oh, my God!

190
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:27,145
Big mistake, though, showing it to me.

191
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:28,605
But who do I phone?

192
00:11:28,730 --> 00:11:29,939
'Cause I've got a remote control.

193
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:31,649
Cease transmission!

194
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,151
Doctor, what number are you on?

195
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:37,447
You haven't even got a number!

196
00:11:37,572 --> 00:11:41,784
Remove the box from the war room,
beyond the transmission field.

197
00:11:42,118 --> 00:11:44,370
Oh, well, that achieved nothing.

198
00:11:44,454 --> 00:11:46,456
Oh, you'd be surprised.

199
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:48,374
(CRASHING)

200
00:11:52,545 --> 00:11:54,047
But what do I do?

201
00:11:54,505 --> 00:11:56,716
All this stuff we've been building.

202
00:11:58,259 --> 00:12:01,304
All this invention,
where's it been heading?

203
00:12:01,512 --> 00:12:05,767
Gravity densifiers, hydroponics,
atmospheric conversion, eco-shells,

204
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:08,853
more than enough to build
a brand new world.

205
00:12:08,937 --> 00:12:11,564
Luke, we haven't got time for this.
I've got to find my parents.

206
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:14,484
Oh, but this isn't just theory.

207
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:18,988
I'm talking planet fall, for all of us.

208
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:21,699
A brand new start
for a brand new human race.

209
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:22,992
Look.

210
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:30,792
A new world, far out, beyond
Alpha Geminorum just waiting for us.

211
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:33,544
Its official designation is Castor 36.

212
00:12:33,628 --> 00:12:37,423
I think of it as Earth-point-2.

213
00:12:38,841 --> 00:12:43,221
I did wonder about Rattigan's World,
but we can take a vote on that.

214
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:45,181
What the hell are you on about?

215
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:46,307
This is where we're going.

216
00:12:46,391 --> 00:12:48,601
I have partners
willing to take us there.

217
00:12:48,685 --> 00:12:51,938
Oh, he's lost it.
I haven't got time for this.

218
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:54,357
Excuse me, I haven't finished.
Where are you going?

219
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:56,359
-To find my brother.
-I didn't say you could leave.

220
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:58,611
I told him to put Atmos in his car.

221
00:12:58,695 --> 00:13:00,613
I've got to go and help him.

222
00:13:00,697 --> 00:13:02,532
Stay where you are!

223
00:13:03,241 --> 00:13:04,534
What do you think you're doing?

224
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,619
Luke, put that down.

225
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:08,830
But...

226
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:12,208
I did this for you. Don't you see?

227
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:15,878
We've spent all our lives excluded,
the clever ones.

228
00:13:16,296 --> 00:13:19,007
They laughed at us and pulled us down,

229
00:13:19,090 --> 00:13:21,843
those ordinary people out there,
those cattle.

230
00:13:23,094 --> 00:13:26,639
This is our chance to leave them behind.

231
00:13:26,723 --> 00:13:27,932
You mean you want them dead?

232
00:13:28,016 --> 00:13:30,310
And I choose you to survive.

233
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:34,564
With planet fall, we can start again.

234
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:39,319
We can build and breed.
We can prosper. We can do anything!

235
00:13:39,402 --> 00:13:40,778
We're going to breed?

236
00:13:40,862 --> 00:13:42,530
I've designed a mating program.

237
00:13:42,613 --> 00:13:43,948
I've planned the whole thing.

238
00:13:44,032 --> 00:13:45,908
Well, then, shoot me.

239
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:49,162
Stay where you are.

240
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,997
Stay where you are, I said.

241
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:54,834
Stay where you are!
Stay where you are! That's an order!

242
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:02,633
Castor 367

243
00:14:05,762 --> 00:14:07,472
You're just sick.

244
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,519
I guess that just proves it.

245
00:14:13,728 --> 00:14:15,688
I'm cleverer than you!

246
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:18,441
I'm cleverer than everyone!
Do you hear me?

247
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:19,984
I'm clever!

248
00:14:20,109 --> 00:14:23,863
The United Nations has issued
a directive worldwide,

249
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:27,325
telling urban populations
to stay indoors.

250
00:14:27,742 --> 00:14:32,622
Those in rural areas are being ordered
to stay away from all major cities.

251
00:14:32,914 --> 00:14:34,957
There are reports from
every country in Europe

252
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:38,503
of thousands of people walking
across country to escape.

253
00:14:38,628 --> 00:14:43,758
And on the Eastern Seaboard of America,
it's said to be reminiscent of Dunkirk,

254
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:47,095
with boats taking refugees
out into the Atlantic.

255
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:51,599
With the freeways blocked by Atmos cars,
populations of major cities

256
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:55,436
are now walking across open country
to escape the fumes.

257
00:14:55,645 --> 00:14:58,439
It is being likened to
a Biblical plague.

258
00:14:58,523 --> 00:15:01,317
Some are calling this the End of Days.

259
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:11,244
DONNA: Mum, you all right?

260
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:13,496
Donna! Where are you, sweetheart?

261
00:15:13,579 --> 00:15:16,374
-Is that her?
-Oh, just finish the job.

262
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:20,545
Your granddad's sealing us in.
He's sealing the windows.

263
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:23,673
Our own house, and we're sealed in.

264
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:28,136
All those things they said about
pollution and ozone and carbon,

265
00:15:28,219 --> 00:15:30,805
they're really happening, aren't they?

266
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:34,183
There's people working on it, Mum.
They're gonna fix it, I promise.

267
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:36,144
Oh, like you'd know. You're so clever.

268
00:15:36,227 --> 00:15:37,770
Oh, don't start.

269
00:15:37,854 --> 00:15:39,439
Please, don't.

270
00:15:39,689 --> 00:15:41,107
I'm sorry.

271
00:15:41,983 --> 00:15:43,067
I wish you were here.

272
00:15:43,151 --> 00:15:46,028
Oh, come on, Sylvia.
Look, that doesn't help.

273
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:48,072
Donna, where are you?

274
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:54,245
It's sort of hard to say. You all right?

275
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:57,290
Yeah, fighting fit, yeah.
Is he with you, the Doctor?

276
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:59,459
SYLVIA: Oh, the Doctor.

277
00:16:00,543 --> 00:16:01,711
No.

278
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:03,963
I'm all on my own.

279
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:07,133
Look, you promised he was going to
look after you.

280
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:08,968
He will, Gramps.

281
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:11,888
There's something he needs me to do.
I just don't know what.

282
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:13,306
Well, I mean,
the whole place is covered,

283
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:16,893
the whole of London, they're saying,
and now the whole world.

284
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:20,480
It's the scale of it, Donna.
I mean, how can one man stop all that?

285
00:16:20,563 --> 00:16:22,690
Trust me, he can do it.

286
00:16:23,316 --> 00:16:27,403
Yeah, well, if he doesn't, you tell him
he'll have to answer to me.

287
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,280
I will.

288
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:32,909
Just as soon as I see him.

289
00:16:33,493 --> 00:16:35,077
I'll tell him.

290
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:36,787
(GASPING)

291
00:16:48,216 --> 00:16:49,634
(COUGHING)

292
00:17:02,897 --> 00:17:07,735
Carbon monoxide, hydrocarbons,
nitrogen oxides, but 10% unidentified.

293
00:17:07,818 --> 00:17:10,238
Some sort of artificial heavy element
we can't trace.

294
00:17:10,321 --> 00:17:11,364
You ever seen anything like it?

295
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:13,032
Must be something
the Sontarans invented.

296
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:15,952
This isn't just poison.
They need this gas for something else.

297
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:17,870
-What could that be?
-Launch grid online and active.

298
00:17:17,954 --> 00:17:20,540
Positions, ladies and gentlemen.
DEFCON 1 initiatives in progress.

299
00:17:20,623 --> 00:17:22,542
What? I told you not to launch!

300
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:26,629
The gas is at 60% density.
80% and people start dying, Doctor.

301
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:28,589
We've got no choice.

302
00:17:28,798 --> 00:17:30,466
Launching in 60,

303
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:37,723
59, 58, 57, 56...

304
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:43,688
Worldwide nuclear grid now coordinating
in 54, 53...

305
00:17:44,105 --> 00:17:48,442
Ha! The planet is going nuclear!
I admire them.

306
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:52,029
The bravery of idiots
is bravery, nonetheless.

307
00:17:52,405 --> 00:17:54,824
The operative is in place, sir.

308
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:57,994
Commander Skorr,
is the attack squad ready?

309
00:17:58,286 --> 00:18:01,163
Ready and eager for battle, sir.
We've been watching for long enough.

310
00:18:01,247 --> 00:18:02,456
It'll be good to taste blood.

311
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:06,961
You're making a mistake, Colonel.

312
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:09,005
For once, I hope the Sontarans are
ahead of you.

313
00:18:09,088 --> 00:18:13,968
North America, online.
United Kingdom, online.

314
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:18,431
France, online. India, online,

315
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:25,187
Pakistan, online. China, online.
North Korea, online.

316
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:27,898
All systems locked and coordinated.

317
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:34,280
Launching in 10, 9, 8, 7,

318
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:36,032
6, 5...

319
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,158
God save us.

320
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:42,330
.4,3,2,1,0.

321
00:18:51,881 --> 00:18:54,050
What is it? What happened?

322
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,469
Did we launch? Well, did we?

323
00:18:56,552 --> 00:18:58,137
Negative, sir.

324
00:18:58,554 --> 00:19:00,973
The launch codes have been wiped, sir.
It must be the Sontarans.

325
00:19:01,057 --> 00:19:02,892
Can we override it?

326
00:19:03,184 --> 00:19:05,853
-Trying it now, sir.
-Missiles wouldn't even dent that ship,

327
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:08,856
so why are the Sontarans
so keen to stop you?

328
00:19:08,939 --> 00:19:10,358
Any ideas?

329
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:12,652
How should I know?

330
00:19:12,777 --> 00:19:14,945
Now, protect the operative.

331
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,425
Stinking out there.

332
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:42,264
Shh! Keep it down, lads.

333
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:45,226
Enemy within! At arms!

334
00:19:45,309 --> 00:19:47,728
Greyhound 40 declaring
absolute emergency.

335
00:19:47,812 --> 00:19:51,524
Sontarans within factory grounds.
East corridor, grid 6.

336
00:19:51,732 --> 00:19:55,277
Absolute emergency. Declaring Code Red.
All troops, Code Red.

337
00:19:55,444 --> 00:19:57,363
Get them out of there.

338
00:19:58,698 --> 00:20:00,658
All troops, open fire.

339
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:05,454
The guns aren't working.

340
00:20:05,538 --> 00:20:08,833
Inform all troops,
standard weapons do not work.

341
00:20:09,959 --> 00:20:11,460
(SCREAMING)

342
00:20:13,504 --> 00:20:16,173
Tell the Doctor
it's that Cordolaine signal.

343
00:20:16,257 --> 00:20:18,634
He's the only one who can stop them.

344
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:26,308
(STATIC ON RADIO)

345
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:30,938
Greyhound 40, report. Over.

346
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,400
Greyhound 40, report.

347
00:20:36,986 --> 00:20:38,904
Greyhound 40, report.

348
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:44,034
He wasn't Greyhound 40.
His name was Ross.

349
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:48,539
Now listen to me,
and get them out of there!

350
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:55,254
Trap One, to all stations. Retreat.

351
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,548
Order imperative. Immediate retreat.

352
00:20:58,382 --> 00:21:00,134
Retreat! Retreat!

353
00:21:14,023 --> 00:21:16,108
Reporting for duty, sir.

354
00:21:21,447 --> 00:21:22,782
This is too easy.

355
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:25,701
They're running like slimebait
from a speelfox.

356
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:44,386
This isn't war! This is sport!

357
00:21:50,392 --> 00:21:52,061
They've taken the factory.

358
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:55,898
Why? They don't need it.
Why attack now? What are they up to?

359
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:58,484
At times like this,
I could do with the Brigadier.

360
00:21:58,567 --> 00:21:59,610
No offence.

361
00:21:59,693 --> 00:22:02,696
None taken. Sir Alistair's a fine man,
if not the best.

362
00:22:02,780 --> 00:22:05,324
Unfortunately, he's stranded in Peru.

363
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:07,493
Launch grid back online.

364
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:15,626
They're inside the system, sir.

365
00:22:15,751 --> 00:22:17,962
It's coming from within UNIT itself.

366
00:22:18,087 --> 00:22:20,589
Trace it. Find out where
it's coming from, and quickly.

367
00:22:20,673 --> 00:22:21,715
Gas levels?

368
00:22:21,799 --> 00:22:25,594
66% in major population areas,
and rising.

369
00:22:26,679 --> 00:22:30,558
Commander Skorr reports victory,
with many glorious deaths.

370
00:22:32,309 --> 00:22:35,354
Sorry to report, sir, I've failed.

371
00:22:37,648 --> 00:22:38,899
They wouldn't come.

372
00:22:38,983 --> 00:22:42,403
The students, they didn't have
the imagination to believe.

373
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:43,737
A pity.

374
00:22:45,155 --> 00:22:47,533
We've lost our target practice.

375
00:22:48,742 --> 00:22:49,827
What do you mean?

376
00:22:49,952 --> 00:22:54,456
Upon arrival on board this ship,
your students would have been shot down.

377
00:22:54,707 --> 00:22:57,918
Perhaps they were more clever
than you thought.

378
00:22:59,837 --> 00:23:02,631
-You promised.
-There was no planet fall.

379
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:05,968
Castor 36, indeed!

380
00:23:06,093 --> 00:23:09,638
We only needed you for installation
of the Atmos system.

381
00:23:09,722 --> 00:23:11,891
No, but I'm on your side.

382
00:23:13,475 --> 00:23:15,769
I did everything you wanted.

383
00:23:16,478 --> 00:23:19,607
And it's not "Atmos system"”.
That's a tautology. It's just "Atmos".

384
00:23:19,690 --> 00:23:21,191
Execute him!

385
00:23:23,319 --> 00:23:25,154
A coward's retreat.

386
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:28,991
Now close all teleport links to Earth.

387
00:23:29,742 --> 00:23:32,536
Isolate them as they perish!

388
00:23:34,163 --> 00:23:35,539
(SOBBING)

389
00:23:47,343 --> 00:23:50,179
Why are they defending the factory
only after we're inside?

390
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:52,681
Because they wanted UNIT here.

391
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:57,353
You gave them something they needed,
something now hidden inside the factory,

392
00:23:57,478 --> 00:23:58,604
something precious.

393
00:23:58,687 --> 00:24:00,189
Then we've got to recover it.

394
00:24:00,272 --> 00:24:02,191
This Cordolaine signal thing,
how does it work?

395
00:24:02,316 --> 00:24:04,193
It's the bullets.
It causes expansion of the copper shell.

396
00:24:04,276 --> 00:24:05,569
Understood. I'm on it.

397
00:24:05,694 --> 00:24:09,323
For the billionth time,
you can't fight Sontarans!

398
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:14,328
A phone. Have you got a phone?

399
00:24:15,913 --> 00:24:17,623
I need your mobile, quickly, hurry up.

400
00:24:23,379 --> 00:24:25,047
(MOBILE RINGING)

401
00:24:27,091 --> 00:24:28,884
What's happened? Where are you?

402
00:24:28,968 --> 00:24:31,178
Still on Earth, but don't worry,
I've got my secret weapon.

403
00:24:31,261 --> 00:24:32,388
-And what's that?
-You.

404
00:24:32,513 --> 00:24:35,391
Hmm, somehow that's not making me happy.

405
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:38,227
Can't you just zap us down to Earth
with that remote thing?

406
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,979
Yeah, I haven't got a remote, though.

407
00:24:40,062 --> 00:24:42,064
I really should,
but I need you on that ship.

408
00:24:42,189 --> 00:24:43,649
That's why I made them move the Tardis.

409
00:24:43,732 --> 00:24:46,068
I'm sorry, but you've got to go outside.

410
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:47,528
But there's Sonterruns out there.

411
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:49,613
Sontarans. But they'll be
on battle stations right now.

412
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,657
They don't exactly walk about
having coffee.

413
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,867
I can talk you through it.

414
00:24:53,951 --> 00:24:55,744
But what if they find me?

415
00:24:55,828 --> 00:24:58,455
I know, and I wouldn't ask,
but there's nothing else I can do.

416
00:24:58,580 --> 00:25:01,166
The whole planet is choking, Donna.

417
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:05,713
What do you need me to do?

418
00:25:05,796 --> 00:25:07,840
The Sontarans are inside the factory,
which means they've got

419
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:09,883
a teleport link with the ship,
and they'll have deadlocked it.

420
00:25:09,967 --> 00:25:11,343
I need you to reopen the link.

421
00:25:11,427 --> 00:25:12,594
I can't even mend a fuse.

422
00:25:12,678 --> 00:25:14,763
Donna, stop talking about yourself
like that.

423
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:17,057
You can do this, I promise.

424
00:25:28,944 --> 00:25:31,363
There's a Sonterrun. A Sontaran.

425
00:25:31,447 --> 00:25:32,865
Did he see you?

426
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:34,033
No, he's got his back to me.

427
00:25:34,116 --> 00:25:36,035
Right, Donna, listen.
On the back of his neck, on his collar,

428
00:25:36,118 --> 00:25:38,454
there's a sort of plug, like a hole,
the Probic Vent.

429
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:40,831
One blow to the Probic Vent
knocks them out.

430
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:42,249
But he's going to kill me.

431
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:46,003
I'm sorry. I swear, I'm so sorry,
but you've got to try.

432
00:26:16,825 --> 00:26:18,535
Back of the neck.

433
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:22,372
Now then, you've got to find the
external junction feed to the teleport.

434
00:26:22,498 --> 00:26:24,333
What does it look like?

435
00:26:24,416 --> 00:26:26,752
Uh, circular panel on the wall,
big symbol on the front,

436
00:26:26,835 --> 00:26:29,254
like a letter "T" with
a horizontal line through it.

437
00:26:29,338 --> 00:26:31,507
Or two "F"s back to back.

438
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,717
Oh, well, there's a door.

439
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:34,843
Should be a switch by the side.

440
00:26:34,927 --> 00:26:36,136
Yeah, there is.

441
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:38,889
But it's Sontaran-shaped,
you need three fingers.

442
00:26:38,972 --> 00:26:40,099
You've got three fingers.

443
00:26:40,182 --> 00:26:41,558
Oh, yeah.

444
00:26:50,234 --> 00:26:51,610
I'm through.

445
00:26:51,693 --> 00:26:54,154
Oh, you are brilliant, you are.

446
00:26:55,531 --> 00:26:56,865
Shut up.

447
00:26:57,199 --> 00:27:00,536
Right, "T" with a line through it.

448
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:04,331
Gotta go. Keep the line open.

449
00:27:04,873 --> 00:27:06,667
I said, you don't stand a chance!

450
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:09,211
Positions. That means everyone.

451
00:27:13,715 --> 00:27:14,842
You're not going without me.

452
00:27:14,925 --> 00:27:16,844
Wouldn't dream of it.

453
00:27:42,744 --> 00:27:44,913
Latest firing stock.
What do you think, Doctor?

454
00:27:44,997 --> 00:27:46,331
Are you my mummy?

455
00:27:46,415 --> 00:27:48,542
If you could concentrate...

456
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:51,795
Bullets with a rad-steel coating,
no copper surface,

457
00:27:51,879 --> 00:27:53,881
should overcome the Cordolaine signal.

458
00:27:53,964 --> 00:27:55,757
But the Sontarans have got lasers.

459
00:27:55,841 --> 00:27:58,552
You can't even see in this fog.
The night-vision doesn't work.

460
00:27:58,635 --> 00:28:01,054
Thank you, Doctor.
Thank you for your lack of faith.

461
00:28:01,138 --> 00:28:03,599
But this time I'm not listening.

462
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:06,268
Attention, all troops.

463
00:28:07,603 --> 00:28:10,105
Sontarans might think of us
as primitive,

464
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:13,650
as does every passing species
with an axe to grind.

465
00:28:13,859 --> 00:28:17,696
They make a mockery of our weapons,
our soldiers, our ideals.

466
00:28:17,779 --> 00:28:19,239
But no more.

467
00:28:19,323 --> 00:28:21,658
From this point on, it stops.

468
00:28:21,909 --> 00:28:25,162
From this point on,
the people of Earth fight back.

469
00:28:25,245 --> 00:28:26,455
And we show them.

470
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:30,042
We show the warriors of Sontar
what the human race can do.

471
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:32,753
Trap One to Hawk Major, go, go, go!

472
00:28:34,171 --> 00:28:35,631
(EXPLOSION)

473
00:28:42,095 --> 00:28:44,640
It's working. The area's clearing.

474
00:28:46,642 --> 00:28:48,477
Engines to maximum!

475
00:28:49,686 --> 00:28:51,480
It's the Valiant.

476
00:28:57,152 --> 00:29:00,656
UNIT carrier ship Valiant
reporting for duty, Doctor,

477
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:04,159
with engines strong enough
to clear away the fog.

478
00:29:15,921 --> 00:29:17,339
(LAUGHING)

479
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:19,174
That's brilliant!

480
00:29:19,258 --> 00:29:21,009
Getting a taste for it, Doctor?

481
00:29:21,134 --> 00:29:22,928
No, not at all. Not me.

482
00:29:23,637 --> 00:29:25,597
Valiant fire at will.

483
00:29:50,747 --> 00:29:52,708
East and north secure. Doctor?

484
00:29:52,791 --> 00:29:55,002
Donna, hold on, I'm coming.

485
00:29:55,836 --> 00:29:57,087
Shouldn't we follow the Colonel?

486
00:29:57,212 --> 00:30:00,424
Ah, you and me, Martha Jones,
just like old times.

487
00:30:00,549 --> 00:30:02,718
Alien technology, this way!

488
00:30:09,182 --> 00:30:12,227
The honour of battle. The glory!

489
00:30:12,936 --> 00:30:14,646
(DEVICE BEEPING)

490
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,864
No Sontarans down here.

491
00:30:24,156 --> 00:30:26,408
They can't resist a battle.

492
00:30:26,533 --> 00:30:27,951
Here we go.

493
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:50,849
Oh, Martha, I'm so sorry.

494
00:30:51,933 --> 00:30:53,393
Still alive.

495
00:30:57,689 --> 00:31:00,359
-Am I supposed to be impressed?
-Wish you carried a gun now?

496
00:31:00,442 --> 00:31:01,777
Not at all.

497
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:04,738
I've been stopping the nuclear launch
all this time.

498
00:31:04,821 --> 00:31:06,865
Doing exactly what I wanted.

499
00:31:06,948 --> 00:31:09,326
I needed to stop the missiles
just as much as the Sontarans.

500
00:31:09,409 --> 00:31:11,828
I'm not having Earth start an
interstellar war. You're a triple agent.

501
00:31:11,912 --> 00:31:14,831
-When did you know?
-About you? Oh, right from the start.

502
00:31:14,915 --> 00:31:16,124
Reduced iris contraction,

503
00:31:16,249 --> 00:31:18,001
slight thinning of the hair follicles
on the left temple,

504
00:31:18,085 --> 00:31:20,212
and frankly, you smell.

505
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:22,255
You might as well have worn a T-shirt
saying "clone”,

506
00:31:22,339 --> 00:31:25,342
although maybe not
in front of Captain Jack.

507
00:31:26,343 --> 00:31:30,514
You remember him, don't you?
'Cause you've got all her memories.

508
00:31:30,806 --> 00:31:33,558
That's why the Sontarans
had to protect her,

509
00:31:33,642 --> 00:31:35,727
to keep you inside UNIT.

510
00:31:36,478 --> 00:31:39,314
Martha Jones is keeping you alive.

511
00:31:44,820 --> 00:31:47,906
All right, all right, I'm here,
I'm here, I've got you, I've got you.

512
00:31:47,989 --> 00:31:50,617
There was this thing, Doctor,
this alien, with this head...

513
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:52,285
(MOBILE RINGING)

514
00:31:52,369 --> 00:31:53,870
Blimey, I'm busy.

515
00:31:53,954 --> 00:31:56,790
-Got it?
-Yes. Now hurry up.

516
00:31:56,998 --> 00:31:58,083
Take off the covering.

517
00:31:58,166 --> 00:32:01,002
All the blue switches inside,
flick them up, like a fuse box.

518
00:32:01,128 --> 00:32:03,505
And that should get
the teleport working.

519
00:32:03,672 --> 00:32:05,549
Oh, my God!

520
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:08,135
That's me.

521
00:32:10,011 --> 00:32:11,972
You will face me, sir.

522
00:32:17,978 --> 00:32:19,396
Wonderful.

523
00:32:29,322 --> 00:32:30,532
Don't touch me.

524
00:32:30,615 --> 00:32:32,367
It's not my fault.

525
00:32:32,451 --> 00:32:36,079
The Sontarans created you,
but you had all my memories.

526
00:32:36,204 --> 00:32:41,042
You've got a brother, sister,
mother and father.

527
00:32:41,376 --> 00:32:44,212
If you don't help me,
they're going to die.

528
00:32:45,297 --> 00:32:47,174
-You love them?
-Yes.

529
00:32:47,424 --> 00:32:48,884
Remember that?

530
00:32:49,009 --> 00:32:50,719
The gas! Tell us about the gas!

531
00:32:50,844 --> 00:32:52,137
He's the enemy!

532
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:55,223
Then tell me.
It's not just poison. What's it for?

533
00:32:55,307 --> 00:32:56,933
Martha, please!

534
00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:03,398
Caesofine concentrate.

535
00:33:04,274 --> 00:33:07,903
It's one part Bosteen,
two parts Probic 5.

536
00:33:08,069 --> 00:33:10,447
Clonefeed! It's clone feed!

537
00:33:10,614 --> 00:33:11,656
What's clone feed?

538
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:14,534
Like amniotic fluid for Sontarans.
That's why they're not invading.

539
00:33:14,618 --> 00:33:18,246
They're converting the atmosphere,
changing the planet into a clone world.

540
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:20,749
Earth becomes a very big hatchery
'cause the Sontarans are clones.

541
00:33:20,832 --> 00:33:22,501
That's how they reproduce.

542
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:26,129
Give them a planet this big,
they'll create billions of new soldiers.

543
00:33:26,213 --> 00:33:28,673
The gas isn't poison, it's food!

544
00:33:30,509 --> 00:33:33,720
My heart, it's getting slower.

545
00:33:34,763 --> 00:33:36,806
There's nothing I can do.

546
00:33:36,890 --> 00:33:39,226
In your mind, you've got so many plans.

547
00:33:39,309 --> 00:33:41,228
There's so much that you want to do.

548
00:33:41,311 --> 00:33:42,646
And I will.

549
00:33:42,729 --> 00:33:45,148
Never do tomorrow what you can do today,
my mum says.

550
00:33:45,232 --> 00:33:48,151
'Cause you never know
how long you've got.

551
00:33:50,445 --> 00:33:54,157
Martha Jones, all that life.

552
00:34:27,107 --> 00:34:28,483
Doctor!

553
00:34:31,486 --> 00:34:33,363
Blue switches done.

554
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:37,993
But they've found me.

555
00:34:38,493 --> 00:34:39,619
Now!

556
00:34:44,833 --> 00:34:47,252
Have I ever told you
how much I hate you?

557
00:34:47,335 --> 00:34:49,129
Hold on! Hold on!
Get off me! Get off me!

558
00:34:49,212 --> 00:34:51,006
Got to bring the Tardis down.

559
00:34:55,677 --> 00:34:57,387
Right. Now, Martha, are you coming?

560
00:34:57,512 --> 00:34:59,598
What about this nuclear-launch thing?

561
00:34:59,681 --> 00:35:03,685
Keep pressing "N". Want to keep
those missiles on the ground.

562
00:35:04,561 --> 00:35:07,188
There's two of them.

563
00:35:07,355 --> 00:35:09,107
Yeah. Long story.

564
00:35:10,692 --> 00:35:14,571
Here we go! The old team back together!
Well, the new team.

565
00:35:14,779 --> 00:35:15,947
We're not going back on that ship!

566
00:35:16,031 --> 00:35:20,577
No, no, no, I need to get the teleport
working so that we can get to...

567
00:35:21,911 --> 00:35:24,956
Here. The Rattigan Academy, owned by...

568
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:27,083
Don't tell anyone what I did.
It wasn't my fault.

569
00:35:27,167 --> 00:35:28,418
The Sontarans lied to me. They...

570
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:30,587
If I see one more gun...

571
00:35:35,884 --> 00:35:39,179
You know, that coat sort of works.

572
00:35:39,554 --> 00:35:41,473
I feel like a kid in my dad's clothes.

573
00:35:41,556 --> 00:35:44,142
Oh, well, if you're calling him Dad,
you're definitely getting over him.

574
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:48,938
The human female on board ship.
It could only be the Doctor's work,

575
00:35:49,022 --> 00:35:52,067
and all the teleport systems
have been deadlocked open.

576
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:56,237
No matter.
Increase the Atmos devices to maximum.

577
00:35:56,488 --> 00:35:57,906
Choke them.

578
00:35:57,989 --> 00:36:01,534
Behold, the clone world is born.

579
00:36:13,630 --> 00:36:15,090
(COUGHING)

580
00:36:20,637 --> 00:36:23,932
Ah, my little girl.
Come on, we'll be all right.

581
00:36:24,015 --> 00:36:25,058
(SOBBING)

582
00:36:25,183 --> 00:36:28,436
We'll be all right. Donna said so.
She promised.

583
00:36:29,604 --> 00:36:32,440
Come on, darling. It's all right.

584
00:36:32,565 --> 00:36:34,484
That's why the Sontarans wanted
to stop the missiles.

585
00:36:34,609 --> 00:36:36,611
They were holding back.

586
00:36:37,779 --> 00:36:39,364
Because the caesofine gas is volatile,

587
00:36:39,447 --> 00:36:41,574
that's why they had to use you
to stop the nuclear attack.

588
00:36:41,658 --> 00:36:43,535
Ground-to-air engagement
could've sparked off the whole thing.

589
00:36:43,618 --> 00:36:44,994
What, like set fire to the atmosphere?

590
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:47,872
Yeah, they need all the gas intact
to breed their clone army.

591
00:36:47,956 --> 00:36:50,458
And all the time, we had Luke here,
in his dream factory.

592
00:36:50,542 --> 00:36:51,793
Planning a little trip, were we?

593
00:36:51,876 --> 00:36:53,128
They promised me a new world.

594
00:36:53,253 --> 00:36:56,506
And you were building equipment,
ready to terraform El Mondo Luko,

595
00:36:56,631 --> 00:37:00,468
so that humans could live there
and breathe the air with this.

596
00:37:01,094 --> 00:37:03,179
An atmospheric converter.

597
00:37:06,057 --> 00:37:08,476
Prepare to launch clone pods.

598
00:37:08,893 --> 00:37:12,021
We will breed across
the surface of the Earth

599
00:37:12,147 --> 00:37:14,149
for the glory of Sontar!

600
00:37:26,035 --> 00:37:27,537
That's London.

601
00:37:28,705 --> 00:37:30,582
You can't even see it.

602
00:37:31,291 --> 00:37:32,792
My family's in there.

603
00:37:32,876 --> 00:37:34,335
If I can get this on
the right setting...

604
00:37:34,419 --> 00:37:36,671
Doctor, hold on.
You said the atmosphere would ignite.

605
00:37:36,755 --> 00:37:38,757
Yeah, I did, didn't I?

606
00:37:54,773 --> 00:37:57,901
Please, please, please, please,
please, please.

607
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:16,085
General Staal, sir...

608
00:38:16,336 --> 00:38:18,046
What's happening?

609
00:38:54,707 --> 00:38:57,085
(PEOPLE CHEERING AND LAUGHING)

610
00:38:59,462 --> 00:39:00,880
(LAUGHING)

611
00:39:02,924 --> 00:39:04,425
(WHISTLING)

612
00:39:10,098 --> 00:39:11,724
(ALL CHEERING)

613
00:39:21,776 --> 00:39:23,361
He's a genius.

614
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:25,613
Just brilliant.

615
00:39:25,738 --> 00:39:27,657
Now we're in trouble.

616
00:39:28,950 --> 00:39:33,413
It seems we must revert to basic
Sontaran stratagem 1.

617
00:39:33,496 --> 00:39:35,540
We will ravage this planet.

618
00:39:35,623 --> 00:39:40,587
Prepare weapons, wipe them out!
Every last stinking human beast!

619
00:39:43,131 --> 00:39:46,467
Right. So, Donna,
thank you for everything.

620
00:39:49,429 --> 00:39:51,472
Martha, you, too. Oh...

621
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,267
So many times.

622
00:39:56,227 --> 00:39:58,897
Luke, do something clever
with your life.

623
00:40:01,608 --> 00:40:02,984
You're saying goodbye.

624
00:40:03,067 --> 00:40:05,403
Sontarans are never defeated.

625
00:40:05,486 --> 00:40:07,572
They'll be getting ready for war.

626
00:40:07,655 --> 00:40:11,910
And well, you know, I've recalibrated
this for Sontaran air, so...

627
00:40:13,620 --> 00:40:15,914
You're going to ignite them?

628
00:40:18,583 --> 00:40:20,335
You'll kill yourself.

629
00:40:20,460 --> 00:40:24,923
Just send that thing up on its own.
I don't know. Put it on a delay.

630
00:40:26,507 --> 00:40:27,842
I can't.

631
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:32,013
Why not?

632
00:40:33,306 --> 00:40:35,725
I've got to give them a choice.

633
00:41:01,459 --> 00:41:03,044
Oh, excellent!

634
00:41:04,087 --> 00:41:06,381
General Staal, you know what this is.

635
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:10,468
But there's one more option.
You can go. Just leave.

636
00:41:11,177 --> 00:41:13,471
Sontaran High Command need never know
what happened here.

637
00:41:13,554 --> 00:41:17,767
Your stratagem would be wise
if Sontarans feared death,

638
00:41:17,892 --> 00:41:19,310
but we do not.

639
00:41:19,394 --> 00:41:20,728
At arms!

640
00:41:25,733 --> 00:41:27,986
I'll do it, Staal.
If it saves the Earth, I'll do it.

641
00:41:28,069 --> 00:41:30,154
A warrior doesn't talk. He acts.

642
00:41:30,238 --> 00:41:31,990
I am giving you the chance to leave.

643
00:41:32,073 --> 00:41:34,200
And miss the glory of this moment?

644
00:41:34,283 --> 00:41:36,953
All weapons targeting Earth, sir.
Firing in 20.

645
00:41:37,036 --> 00:41:39,038
-I'm warning you!
-And I salute you!

646
00:41:39,122 --> 00:41:40,456
Take aim!

647
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:43,126
Shoot me, I'm still going to press this.
You'll die, Staal.

648
00:41:43,251 --> 00:41:44,794
Knowing that you died, too.

649
00:41:44,877 --> 00:41:45,920
Firing in 15.

650
00:41:46,004 --> 00:41:47,755
For the glory of Sontar!

651
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:55,096
(ALL CHANTING) Sontar-ha!

652
00:41:58,266 --> 00:42:00,727
(ALL CHANTING) Sontar-ha!

653
00:42:00,810 --> 00:42:02,854
I'll do it! I'll do it!

654
00:42:03,104 --> 00:42:04,981
(CIRCUITRY CHIRPING)

655
00:42:05,189 --> 00:42:07,775
-What are you doing?
-Something clever.

656
00:42:09,068 --> 00:42:10,194
(ALL CHANTING) Sontar-ha!

657
00:42:10,278 --> 00:42:16,701
...nine, eight, seven, six, five, four,
three two...

658
00:42:16,784 --> 00:42:18,411
(CHANTING) Sontar-ha!

659
00:42:18,494 --> 00:42:19,787
...one.

660
00:43:02,872 --> 00:43:04,665
-Morning.
-Morning.

661
00:43:04,749 --> 00:43:08,294
Walked all the way.
Won't catch me driving.

662
00:43:11,964 --> 00:43:15,843
The streets are half empty.
People still aren't driving.

663
00:43:16,010 --> 00:43:19,931
There's kids on bikes
all over the place. It's wonderful.

664
00:43:20,014 --> 00:43:23,935
Unpack that, love.
I'm going to see if Suzette's all right.

665
00:43:28,106 --> 00:43:30,691
I won't tell her. Best not.

666
00:43:33,986 --> 00:43:37,156
Just keep it as our little secret, eh?

667
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:38,449
Yeah.

668
00:43:39,742 --> 00:43:42,829
And you go with him,
that wonderful Doctor.

669
00:43:44,122 --> 00:43:46,249
You go and see the stars.

670
00:43:50,628 --> 00:43:54,298
And then bring a bit of them back
for your old gramps.

671
00:44:11,983 --> 00:44:13,317
Love you.

672
00:44:20,741 --> 00:44:22,118
(SIGHING)

673
00:44:26,205 --> 00:44:27,748
How were they?

674
00:44:27,915 --> 00:44:29,125
Oh...

675
00:44:30,793 --> 00:44:32,420
Same old stuff.

676
00:44:34,463 --> 00:44:35,673
They're fine.

677
00:44:35,756 --> 00:44:38,009
So, you gonna come with us?

678
00:44:38,092 --> 00:44:40,511
We're not exactly short of space.

679
00:44:40,595 --> 00:44:43,598
Oh, I have missed all this,
but, you know...

680
00:44:44,557 --> 00:44:47,435
I'm good here, back at home.

681
00:44:48,436 --> 00:44:51,105
And I'm better for having been away.

682
00:44:51,189 --> 00:44:53,608
Besides, someone needs me.

683
00:44:53,691 --> 00:44:56,986
Never mind the universe, I've got
a great big world of my own now.

684
00:44:58,404 --> 00:44:59,822
(SCREAMING)

685
00:45:01,657 --> 00:45:03,117
What? What?

686
00:45:05,828 --> 00:45:07,455
Doctor, don't you dare!

687
00:45:07,538 --> 00:45:09,999
No, no, I didn't touch anything!

688
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:12,418
We're in flight! It's not me!

689
00:45:13,211 --> 00:45:14,670
Where are we going?

690
00:45:14,754 --> 00:45:17,131
I don't know. It's out of control!

691
00:45:17,548 --> 00:45:19,800
(MARTHA CRYING OUT)

692
00:45:20,968 --> 00:45:22,887
Doctor, just listen to me!

693
00:45:22,970 --> 00:45:25,848
You take me home!
Take me home right now!

694
00:45:38,361 --> 00:45:40,321
Where did she come from?

695
00:45:40,404 --> 00:45:41,739
From me.

696
00:45:42,198 --> 00:45:43,616
From you?

697
00:45:44,033 --> 00:45:45,201
How?

698
00:45:47,828 --> 00:45:49,121
Well...

699
00:45:50,748 --> 00:45:53,000
I'd like to see you try that.

700
00:45:56,837 --> 00:45:58,673
She's my daughter.

701
00:46:00,174 --> 00:46:01,634
Hello, Dad.

